enturies? What did monks and nuns perceive as the limitations of monastic prayer and meditation, and how did they understand their own imperfections and failures to perform "perfect" devotion? What extra-textual tools—art, manuscripts, diagrams, spaces—did monks and nuns rely upon to stimulate their practices of meditation? What does monastic meditation reveal about the emotional lives of Benedictine and Cistercian monks and nuns in the high Middle Ages? And, finally, what does the monastic struggle to pursue a prayerful Christian life have to teach the secular world of the twenty-first century?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnglican monasticism and religious ordersxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMeditationxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPrayerxAnglican ChurchxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPrayerxAnglican churchxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aRELIGION / Monasticism.2bisacsh  aHistory of Emotions, Monasticism, Medieval Christianity, asceticism,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802701074?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802701074423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802701074/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish 